CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 19, 1959, pg. A3, reads: "Bon Ami Paraders - Among the official cars included in spectacular parade of the Elks' Lodge recently was this handsome convertible, which was sponsored by the Hostess Club of Bon Ami Temple 49. The 'precious cargo' includes the president, Mrs. Alberta G. Terrell, who is seated on top.  Others, left to right, are Mrs. Pearl Ashby, Levenia Lemons, Clara Penn and Jack Lankford. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Alberta G. Terrell wearing strapless gown seated on back of Cadillac Eldorado convertible, with Pearl Ashby, Levenia Lemons, Clara Penn, and Jack Lankford inside, and banner inscribed "Bon Ami Temple no. 49, Hostess Club," in Elks parade
